,{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Same event in same state always produces same result"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transition Rules"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Current State: gather_info\nEvent: \"intent is technical\"\n    ↓\nTransition → Next State: action_resolve"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example"},{"type":"text","text":": \"if intent is technical, go to action_resolve\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How It Works: Complete Flow"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Define states (nodes) with execution logic per state\n    ↓\n2. Define transitions (edges) with conditions specifying when to move\n    ↓\n3. Agent runs a state\n    ↓\n4. Agent evaluates transitions\n    ↓\n5. Agent moves to the next state"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Stopping Conditions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit stopping conditions"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Terminal state"},{"type":"text","text":" — normal completion\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Error"},{"type":"text","text":" — failure occurred\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Budget"},{"type":"text","text":" — token/time budget exhausted"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation Example: YAML Configuration"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sample State Machine"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"initial_state:\n  messages:\n    - role: system\n      content: \"Answer using Google and Wikipedia as needed.\"\n\nstates:\n  search_chat:\n    # User Message Handling\n    get_new_user_message: Formats user input\n    add_user_message: Inserts into conversation history\n    \n    # Retrieving Search Results\n    search_generation: Calls Google Search + Wikipedia\n    \n    # Processing Results\n    add_tool_and_asst_msgs: Merges results with history\n    \n    # Generating Final Response\n    llm_call: Extracts latest message\n    \n    # Write to State\n    write_to_state:\n      messages: add_tool_and_asst_msgs\n    \n    # Transition to Next State\n    next_node:\n      default: search_chat  # Loops back for continuous interaction"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What this does"},{"type":"text","text":":\n1. Accepts user message as input\n2. Searches Google and Wikipedia for context\n3. Processes results, appends to conversation\n4. Generates final LLM response\n5. Loops back to continue conversation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Example: Customer Service Agent"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5-State Flow"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"triage → info_gather → action_resolve → verify → escalate"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Each state has"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Own prompt\n- Own tool set (e.g., "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"gather_info"},{"type":"text","text":" has different tools than "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"verify"},{"type":"text","text":")\n- Clear entry/exit conditions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Transitions are guards on agent output"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- \"if intent is technical → go to action_resolve\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Debugging Benefit"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Before"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Agent went off-track somewhere\"\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"After"},{"type":"text","text":": \"Agent looped between info_gather and action_resolve\""}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Error Handling"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Error State Pattern"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"If act node fails\n    ↓\nTransition to error state\n    ↓\nIn error: attempt recovery OR fall back to default answer"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Prevents agent from crashing\n- Defines error states and recovery transitions\n- If API call fails, transitions to error state instead of retrying indefinitely"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"With Error State"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Start → Working → Success → Done\n       ↓\n    (Error) → Recovery → Done"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Advanced Features"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Subgraphs (Nested State Machines)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Large agent\n    ↓\n'set' state = subgraph with own think→act→verify loop\n    ↓\nWhen subgraph finishes, returns to parent"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"LangGraph supports subgraphs via "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"add_subgraph"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Checkpointing"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Using LangGraph's checkpointing\n    ↓\nState machine can survive restarts\n    ↓\nCrucial for long-running agents (minutes/hours)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Timeout State"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"After certain idle period\n    ↓\nAgent transitions to timeout state"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Testing & Debugging"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Unit Testing"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Because state machines have explicit states:\n    ↓\nCan unit test each node in isolation\n    ↓\nSimulate inputs and check state transitions"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Inspection"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use app.get_state to inspect current state\n    ↓\nMakes debugging much easier than linear agents"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefits"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why It Works"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Predictability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clear flow to defined stages"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Observability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Debugging becomes \"which state failed\""}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Testability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can unit test each node in isolation"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Auditability"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Behavior explicit and testable"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Error Handling"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Define error states + recovery transitions"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Mental Model"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of agent states and transitions like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"a pinball machine"},{"type":"text","text":": the agent is the pinball, states are the bumpers/tracks it can land on, and transitions are the rules that determine which track it rolls to next. If the pinball hits a \"technical\" bumper, it goes to the \"action_resolve\" ramp. If it hits an \"error\" bumper, it drops to recovery. The pinball can only be on one track at a time, and the path is completely predictable."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"State machine = structured execution as named states with explicit transitions [gather_info → plan → execute → verify → done]"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"States = distinct modes with clear entry/behavior/exit logic"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transitions = rules specifying when to move between states"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agent runs state → evaluates transitions → moves to next state"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Stopping conditions: terminal state, error, or budget"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Tools/prompts scoped per-state (e.g., gather_info has different tools than verify)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Design: mutually exclusive, complete coverage, meaningful names, balance"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Transitions are: event-triggered, atomic, deterministic"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Error handling: define error state + recovery transitions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Subgraphs: nested state machines (e.g., set state = think→act→verify loop)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Checkpointing: state machine survives restarts (crucial for long-running agents)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Timeout: after idle period, transitions to timeout state"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Testing: unit test each node in isolation, simulate inputs, check transitions"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Verification: use app.get_state to inspect current state"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Benefit: debugging becomes \"which state failed\" not \"where did agent wander\""}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"State machines constrain flow to defined stages, making agent behavior explicit, testable, and predictable — debugging shifts from \"where did it wander\" to \"which state failed\"."}]}]}}
